The England seamers again will try and bowl dot balls in the channel to force him to play straight and edge. He plays lots of balls square of the wicket, away from his body, making him very vulnerable to an edge. He does not play side-on defensive shots which means he is playing away from his eye line, so any movement of the ball is dangerous.
